---

<BaseLayout
  title="Peptide Discovery Tool | Wikipept"
  description="Interactive peptide discovery tool — search 50+ peptides by half-life, charge, hydrophobicity, class, and indication. Find peptides matching your research criteria."
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(howToJsonLd)} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(faqJsonLd)} />

  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 py-8">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Peptide Discovery Tool</h1>
    <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-8">
      Search 50+ peptides by physicochemical properties, class, and indication.
      Filter by half-life, charge, hydrophobicity, and more.
    </p>

    <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg shadow-md p-6 mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Filters</h2>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 mb-6">
        <div>
          <label for="class-filter" class="block text-sm font-medium mb-2">Peptide Class</label>
          <select id="class-filter" class="w-full px-4 py-2 border border-gray-300 dark:border-gray-600 rounded-lg focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500 dark:bg-gray-700">
            <option value="">All Classes</option>
            <option value="GLP-1 RA">GLP-1 Receptor Agonists</option>
            <option value="Dual GIP/GLP-1">Dual GIP/GLP-1 Agonists</option>
            <option value="Oral GLP-1">Oral GLP-1 Agonists</option>
            <option value="Triple Agonist">Triple Agonists</option>
            <option value="Dual GCGR/GLP-1">Dual GCGR/GLP-1</option>
            <option value="Amylin Analog">Amylin Analogues</option>
            <option value="Rapid-Acting Insulin">Rapid-Acting Insulin</option>
            <option value="Long-Acting Insulin">Long-Acting Insulin</option>
            <option value="Ultra-Long Insulin">Ultra-Long Insulin</option>
            <option value="Weekly Insulin">Weekly Insulin</option>
            <option value="GHRH Analogue">GHRH Analogues</option>
            <option value="GHS (Ghrelin Mimetic)">Ghrelin Mimetics</option>
            <option value="Non-Peptide GHS">Non-Peptide GHS</option>
            <option value="Repair Peptide">Repair Peptides</option>
            <option value="Melanocortin">Melanocortin Analogs</option>
            <option value="Neuropeptide">Neuropeptides</option>
            <option value="Vasopressin Analog">Vasopressin Analogs</option>
            <option value="Thymic Peptide">Thymic Peptides</option>
            <option value="Somatostatin Analog">Somatostatin Analogs</option>
            <option value="Natriuretic Peptide">Natriuretic Peptides</option>
            <option value="Antiplatelet Peptide">Antiplatelet Peptides</option>
          </select>
        </div>

        <div>
          <label for="indication-filter" class="block text-sm font-medium mb-2">Indication</label>
          <select id="indication-filter" class="w-full px-4 py-2 border border-gray-300 dark:border-gray-600 rounded-lg focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500 dark:bg-gray-700">
            <option value="">All Indications</option>
            <option value="T2D">Type 2 Diabetes</option>
            <option value="T1D">Type 1 Diabetes</option>
            <option value="Obesity">Obesity</option>
            <option value="GH deficiency">GH Deficiency</option>
            <option value="Tissue repair">Tissue Repair</option>
            <option value="EPP">Erythropoietic Protoporphyria</option>
            <option value="FSD">Female Sexual Dysfunction</option>
            <option value="ED">Erectile Dysfunction</option>
            <option value="Acromegaly">Acromegaly</option>
            <option value="Heart failure">Heart Failure</option>
            <option value="Immunomodulation">Immunomodulation</option>
            <option value="Labor">Labor Induction</option>
            <option value="ACS">Acute Coronary Syndrome</option>
          </select>
        </div>

        <div>
          <label for="approved-filter" class="block text-sm font-medium mb-2">Approval Status</label>
          <select id="approved-filter" class="w-full px-4 py-2 border border-gray-300 dark:border-gray-600 rounded-lg focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500 dark:bg-gray-700">
            <option value="">All</option>
            <option value="true">FDA Approved</option>
            <option value="false">Research/Investigational</option>
          </select>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 mb-6">
        <div>
          <label for="half-life-min" class="block text-sm font-medium mb-2">Min Half-Life (hours)</label>
          <input type="number" id="half-life-min" placeholder="0" min="0" class="w-full px-4 py-2 border border-gray-300 dark:border-gray-600 rounded-lg focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500 dark:bg-gray-700" />
        </div>
        <div>
          <label for="half-life-max" class="block text-sm font-medium mb-2">Max Half-Life (hours)</label>
          <input type="number" id="half-life-max" placeholder="300" min="0" class="w-full px-4 py-2 border border-gray-300 dark:border-gray-600 rounded-lg focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500 dark:bg-gray-700" />
        </div>
        <div>
          <label for="charge-filter" class="block text-sm font-medium mb-2">Charge at pH 7.4</label>
          <select id="charge-filter" class="w-full px-4 py-2 border border-gray-300 dark:border-gray-600 rounded-lg focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500 dark:bg-gray-700">
            <option value="">Any</option>
            <option value="positive">Positive (+)</option>
            <option value="negative">Negative (−)</option>
            <option value="neutral">Neutral (0)</option>
          </select>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-6">
        <div>
          <label for="search-input" class="block text-sm font-medium mb-2">Search Peptide Name</label>
          <input type="text" id="search-input" placeholder="e.g., Semaglutide" class="w-full px-4 py-2 border border-gray-300 dark:border-gray-600 rounded-lg focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500 dark:bg-gray-700" />
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-end">
          <button id="reset-btn" class="px-6 py-2 bg-gray-500 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-gray-600 mr-2">Reset</button>
          <button id="sort-btn" class="px-6 py-2 bg-blue-500 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-blue-600">Sort by Half-Life</button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div id="results-count" class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-4"></div>

    <div id="results-table" class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full text-sm text-left text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">
        <thead class="text-xs text-gray-700 uppercase bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-700 dark:text-gray-400">
          <tr>
            <th scope="col" class="px-6 py-3">Peptide</th>
            <th scope="col" class="px-6 py-3">Class</th>
            <th scope="col" class="px-6 py-3">Half-Life</th>
            <th scope="col" class="px-6 py-3">MW (Da)</th>
            <th scope="col" class="px-6 py-3">Charge</th>
            <th scope="col" class="px-6 py-3">Route</th>
            <th scope="col" class="px-6 py-3">Indication</th>
            <th scope="col" class="px-6 py-3">Status</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody id="peptide-tbody">
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-8 bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg shadow-md p-6">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">How to Use This Tool</h2>
      <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
        <li>Select a peptide class or indication to narrow results</li>
        <li>Set half-life range to filter by dosing frequency (e.g., 100–300 h for weekly agents)</li>
        <li>Filter by charge to find positively, negatively, or neutrally charged peptides</li>
        <li>Use the search box for direct name matching</li>
        <li>Click "Sort by Half-Life" to order results from shortest to longest half-life</li>
        <li>Click "Reset" to clear all filters</li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-8 bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg shadow-md p-6">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">FAQ</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <details class="group">
          <summary class="cursor-pointer font-medium text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400">How does the peptide discovery tool work?</summary>
          <p class="mt-2 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">The tool searches a database of 50+ peptides filtered by physicochemical properties (half-life, charge, hydrophobicity, molecular weight), peptide class, and clinical indication.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="group">
          <summary class="cursor-pointer font-medium text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400">What peptide classes are included?</summary>
          <p class="mt-2 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">The database includes GLP-1 RAs, GIP agonists, dual GIP/GLP-1 agonists, GHRH analogues, ghrelin mimetics, repair peptides, melanocortin analogues, neuropeptides, thymic peptides, insulin analogues, amylin analogues, somatostatin analogues, and natriuretic peptides.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="group">
          <summary class="cursor-pointer font-medium text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400">Can I search by half-life range?</summary>
          <p class="mt-2 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Yes. Use the Min/Max Half-Life fields to define a range. This helps identify peptides suitable for different dosing frequencies — from ultra-rapid (minutes) to ultra-long-acting (weekly).</p>
        </details>
        <details class="group">
          <summary class="cursor-pointer font-medium text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400">Is this tool for clinical decision-making?</summary>
          <p class="mt-2 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">No. This tool is for educational and research purposes only. It provides pharmacological data but does not constitute medical advice.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <script is:inline>
    const peptideData = [
